  * rejected with -ENOMEM at probe (PR14b regression). We reserve a 64 KiB
- * partition; fman_muram_alloc rounds up to 256-byte (gen_pool
- * min_alloc_order=8) so 65536 is an exact multiple.
+ * partition and sub-allocate every PCD MURAM request from it via a
+ * dedicated gen_pool (min_alloc_order=8 -> 256-byte granule, so 65536 is
+ * an exact multiple).  This bounds PCD allocations to the reserved arena
+ * instead of competing with the global MURAM free list: on LS1046A the
+ * post-CAM/FIFO global free tail is only ~21 KiB, far too small for the
+ * FE/ehash internal-buffer pool (~33 KiB) which DOES fit the 64 KiB
+ * reservation.  Without the sub-pool the reservation was dead-weight and
+ * fman_pcd_muram_alloc() silently fell back to the tiny global tail.
  */
